Coding plan:
"### File Structure
```
SmartHomeManager/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── device_list.html
│   ├── add_device.html
│   ├── device_control.html
│   ├── automation_rules.html
│   ├── energy_report.html
│   └── activity_logs.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   └── js/
│       └── scripts.js
│
└── data/
    ├── users.txt
    ├── devices.txt
    ├── rooms.txt
    ├── automation_rules.txt
    ├── energy_logs.txt
    └── activity_logs.txt
```

### File Descriptions
```
app.py
- The main backend Python file implementing the web application using a framework like Flask.
- Handles routing for all seven pages (Dashboard, Device List, Add Device, Device Control, Automation Rules, Energy Report, Activity Logs).
- Manages reading from and writing to the local text files in the 'data' directory.
- Implements business logic for device management, automation rules, energy consumption monitoring, and activity logging.

templates/
- Contains HTML template files for each page of the web application.
- Each HTML file corresponds to one of the seven pages defined in the requirements.
- Uses Jinja2 templating (or similar) to dynamically render data passed from app.py.

static/css/styles.css
- Contains all CSS styles for the web application to ensure consistent and user-friendly UI design.

static/js/scripts.js
- Contains JavaScript code for client-side interactivity, such as button actions, form validations, and dynamic UI updates.

data/
- Directory to store all application data in text files as specified.
- Files include users.txt, devices.txt, rooms.txt, automation_rules.txt, energy_logs.txt, and activity_logs.txt.
- Each file follows the pipe-delimited format described in the requirements document.
